B.bk={discovery:0,signal:1,prototype:2,build:3,launch:4,iterate:5}
B.Vv=new A.aK("Discovery: Map the unmapped cottage economy","Crawl growth starts with a discovery problem, not a marketing problem: the supply already exists (home bakers, soap makers, knife sharpeners), but it is structurally invisible.\n\nTraditional platforms privilege commercial addresses and global shipping. Crawl measures what they ignore: pop-up hours, finite inventory, residential pickup logic, and hyper-local walkability.\n\nOutput: a neighborhood \u201casset map\u201d that shows where demand concentrates, which categories trigger walking behavior, and where the marketplace can densify into repeat weekly routes.")
B.Vc=new A.aK("Signal: Prove \u201cSaturday morning crawl\u201d activation","The wedge is a fast, visual map that makes hidden commerce feel safe and standard.\n\nWe validate the moment a customer opens the app, sees who is open within a 1-mile radius, and can commit to a pickup without awkward messaging.\n\nSuccess metric: time-to-first-walk (TTFW) \u2014 the first real-world neighborhood visit triggered by the map, not by social feeds.")
B.Wd=new A.aK("Prototype: Open/Closed toggles + crawl routes as behavior design","We prototype the key behavioral mechanic: creators control visibility.\n\nOpen/Closed toggles, scheduled windows, and \u201cporch pickup\u201d instructions make residential commerce predictable. Route previews turn the marketplace into a physical scavenger hunt \u2014 without exposing private addresses outside operating hours.\n\nPrototype success: users feel guided (not creeped out), and creators feel protected (not exposed).")
B.Wg=new A.aK("Build: Density flywheels (events, clusters, repeat circuits)","We build growth as a local density problem.\n\nThe system supports \u201cCrawl Events\u201d (time-boxed neighborhood drops), category-based circuits (bread + coffee + crafts), and notification rails that convert one-off novelty into weekly habit.\n\nIf density rises, the marketplace stops being an app \u2014 it becomes a neighborhood ritual.")
B.VY=new A.aK("Launch: Neighborhood pilots with verifiable safety signals","We launch in pilot neighborhoods where verification has visible meaning.\n\nCreators onboard with license proof; customers see trust badges; cities/communities see structured participation rather than informal chaos.\n\nLaunch story: higher local foot traffic + higher seller consistency + lower \u201cis this safe?\u201d anxiety.")
B.VA=new A.aK("Iterate: Reduce friction until discovery feels inevitable","Iteration removes the reasons people fall back to group chats.\n\nWe tune map clarity, pickup instructions, supply caps, and notification cadence so the experience becomes calmer and more predictable each cycle.\n\nFinish line: customers reliably \u201ccheck Crawl\u201d the way they check the weather \u2014 because it is the neighborhood\u2019s live commerce layer.")
B.Si=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.Vv,B.Vc,B.Wd,B.Wg,B.VY,B.VA],t.F)
B.Wk=new A.aK("Discovery: Monetize the coordination layer (not the craft)","Crawl monetization is not about taxing tiny creators \u2014 it\u2019s about pricing the infrastructure that makes residential commerce legible.\n\nWe validate what creators will pay for: predictable demand, capacity controls, verified trust, and reduced regulatory anxiety.\n\nOutput: a value model spanning listing tiers, transaction rails, and hyper-local ad inventory that is contextual (not spammy).")
B.Vt=new A.aK("Signal: Make payouts + fees feel fair and transparent","We prove that a creator can see \u201cwhat I earned, what I paid, and why\u201d in plain language.\n\nConsumers must see total cost and pickup terms before committing. Creators must see fee policy and payout timing without surprises.\n\nSuccess metric: low dispute rate + high re-listing rate (creators keep coming back).")
B.Vd=new A.aK("Prototype: Capacity caps as a premium control surface","We prototype finite inventory as first-class.\n\nCreators set caps (e.g., 30 loaves/week), sell-out behavior is explicit, and the marketplace doesn\u2019t over-promise. Premium tools include label templates, scheduled drops, and waitlists.\n\nPrototype success: creators avoid overwhelm, customers avoid disappointment \u2014 and monetization aligns with reliability.")
B.W9=new A.aK("Build: Local payments + escrow-like confidence","We build transaction rails that feel as safe as mainstream e-commerce while operating in residential contexts.\n\nClear states (reserved, ready, picked up, refunded) prevent ambiguity. Receipts, tax notes, and category constraints are embedded so creators stay compliant.\n\nThe product becomes a financial utility layer for the cottage economy.")
B.Vz=new A.aK("Launch: Marketplace integrity as the monetization story","We launch monetization around integrity: reliability is what users pay for.\n\nWe measure seller retention, order completion rate, and customer repeat purchases as the core revenue predictors.\n\nIf the platform is trustworthy, monetization becomes sustainable without predatory tactics.")
B.VV=new A.aK("Iterate: Tune for high-signal local ads (brands without noise)","Iteration expands revenue without contaminating trust.\n\nWe tune local ads to be context-aware: ingredient suppliers for bakers, tool suppliers for makers, neighborhood lifestyle partners \u2014 always tied to active foot traffic and creator intent.\n\nWin: ads feel like infrastructure sponsorship, not interruption.")
B.Sl=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.Wk,B.Vt,B.Vd,B.W9,B.Vz,B.VV],t.F)
B.Vh=new A.aK("Discovery: Make compliance a product surface","Crawl operates inside governance terrain: cottage food laws, licensing, labeling, revenue caps, and local zoning norms.\n\nWe map what creators fear (getting shut down, being reported, operating unknowingly out of bounds) and what customers need (proof that \u201chomemade\u201d is legitimate).\n\nOutput: a compliance UX that guides rather than polices.")
B.Wc=new A.aK("Signal: Verification that increases safety without exposing homes","We prove a verification gate that reassures customers while protecting creators.\n\nLicenses can be verified, badges can be shown, but addresses are only revealed during operating windows and only to committed buyers.\n\nSuccess metric: higher conversion on verified listings + lower safety-related drop-off.")
B.W7=new A.aK("Prototype: Policy-aware listing templates","We prototype listing flows that encode the law.\n\nCategory constraints, allergen/ingredient labels, pickup rules, and revenue caps are reflected directly in UI defaults \u2014 reducing accidental non-compliance.\n\nPrototype success: creators feel \u201cguided\u201d instead of \u201cwatched.\u201d")
B.Vb=new A.aK("Build: Audit-ready histories (human-readable)","We build event histories that can answer: who listed what, when, under what license state.\n\nThis supports creators in disputes and gives the platform the right to operate as it scales across municipalities.\n\nGovernance becomes stability: rules are explicit, versioned, and explainable.")
B.W1=new A.aK("Launch: Cities see structure, not informal chaos","We launch governance as legitimacy.\n\nCommunities gain visibility into a previously informal economy; creators gain protection via structured participation; customers gain trust.\n\nLaunch success: fewer complaints + clearer dispute resolution + higher license adoption.")
B.Wn=new A.aK("Iterate: Regional policy tuning + creator education loop","Iteration localizes governance.\n\nWe tune flows per jurisdiction, update templates as laws evolve, and add micro-education that reduces mistakes (labeling, category limits, pickup etiquette).\n\nGoal: compliance that feels like enablement \u2014 and scales region by region.")
B.Sk=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.Vh,B.Wc,B.W7,B.Vb,B.W1,B.Wn],t.F)
B.VG=new A.aK("Discovery: Threat model residential commerce","Security in Crawl is not optional: it\u2019s the boundary between community and harm.\n\nWe map threats: address scraping, stalking risk, fraudulent listings, payment disputes, and inventory spoofing.\n\nOutput: a security model that protects home privacy by default while still enabling legitimate discovery.")
B.W6=new A.aK("Signal: Privacy-first location reveal","We prove that location can be useful without being exposed.\n\nGeo-fenced approximations for browsing; exact pickup details only after commitment; time-window access that expires.\n\nSuccess metric: high browse-to-commit conversion with no increase in privacy incidents.")
B.V9=new A.aK("Prototype: Trust + abuse controls without \u201cparanoia UX\u201d","We prototype reports, blocks, and identity checks that feel calm.\n\nSecurity must not turn the product into a warning screen. Controls are present, clear, and rarely needed \u2014 but strong when invoked.\n\nPrototype success: creators feel safe enough to participate; customers feel confident enough to walk.")
B.Va=new A.aK("Build: Least-privilege access + hardened transaction states","We build strict access boundaries: sensitive location data is segmented and time-scoped.\n\nTransaction state machines prevent ambiguous outcomes; logs support dispute resolution; rate limits prevent scraping.\n\nSecurity becomes an enabling layer, not a drag.")
B.Wi=new A.aK("Launch: Monitoring for scraping + fraud patterns","We launch with monitors tuned to the actual adversary: automated scraping, repeated address requests, suspicious account creation, and chargeback spikes.\n\nWe ship operator playbooks because residential context raises the stakes.\n\nLaunch success: low incident rate + fast response when anomalies appear.")
B.Vy=new A.aK("Iterate: Hardening cycles as the marketplace scales","Iteration strengthens defenses as density increases.\n\nWe adjust heuristics, verification thresholds, and privacy defaults region-by-region.\n\nOutcome: the platform remains safe enough to be normal \u2014 which is the only way it becomes infrastructure.")
B.Sp=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.VG,B.W6,B.V9,B.Va,B.Wi,B.Vy],t.F)
B.W0=new A.aK("Discovery: Engagement is a neighborhood ritual","Engagement in Crawl is not infinite scroll \u2014 it\u2019s real-world walking.\n\nWe map repeatable moments: Saturday morning circuits, seasonal maker drops, and community crawl events.\n\nOutput: an engagement model rooted in place-making and local discovery.")
B.VM=new A.aK("Signal: \u201cWho\u2019s open near me?\u201d as a daily question","We prove a daily-check behavior anchored in utility.\n\nIf the map reliably reflects live availability and finite supply, users return without needing gimmicks.\n\nSuccess metric: weekly active walkers + repeat purchases per neighborhood.")
B.Wl=new A.aK("Prototype: Crawl events as lightweight game mechanics","We prototype events that gamify discovery without turning it into noise.\n\nBadges for completing a circuit, route suggestions, and \u201cdrop windows\u201d create urgency tied to real inventory \u2014 not artificial scarcity.\n\nPrototype success: engagement feels like community participation.")
B.Ve=new A.aK("Build: Notification cadence + inventory truth","We build the engagement engine around truth: inventory and hours must be accurate.\n\nNotifications are opt-in, category-specific, and local \u2014 a utility layer, not a spam channel.\n\nReliability is what keeps people coming back.")
B.W3=new A.aK("Launch: Instrument real-world loop health","We launch measurement that respects the phenomenon: walks, pickups, sell-outs, and repeat circuits.\n\nVanity metrics are avoided because they distort incentives.\n\nIf loop health is strong, the neighborhood becomes the product.")
B.Vu=new A.aK("Iterate: Expand categories without breaking safety + trust","Iteration expands the cottage economy surface area: food, crafts, services.\n\nEach new category requires its own trust and compliance affordances.\n\nWin: more variety and density while the platform stays calm, safe, and legible.")
B.Sj=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.W0,B.VM,B.Wl,B.Ve,B.W3,B.Vu],t.F)
B.SU=new A.aN(B.er,[B.Si,B.Sl,B.Sk,B.Sp,B.Sj],t.mO)
B.V7=new A.aK("Discovery: Map tipping fatigue as a churn engine","TipZero growth starts with a cultural reversal: POS systems turned gratuity into coercion, and customers responded with avoidance, resentment, and lower repeat visits.\n\nWe observe real checkout behavior: where people hesitate on 18\u201325% prompts, how staff braces for awkwardness, and how merchants absorb reputational damage.\n\nOutput: a friction map that treats tipping fatigue as a retention problem \u2014 not a moral debate.")
B.V0=new A.aK("Signal: Prove the zero-pressure default increases return visits","The wedge is simple: make \u201cZero Tip\u201d socially normal and operationally fast.\n\nWe validate that removing the forced prompt reduces checkout dwell time and restores privacy \u2014 while worker bonuses still land via alternative rails.\n\nSuccess metric: repeat-visit lift + faster lines, without worker income collapsing.")
B.Wq=new A.aK("Prototype: \u201cTipZero Certified\u201d as a trust badge","We prototype the network effect: customers seek establishments that don\u2019t tip-shame.\n\nThe experience is a permission slip: pay the base price now, reward later if you choose \u2014 or let sponsors fund the bonus.\n\nPrototype success: sentiment improves instantly and merchants feel safer adopting.")
B.VR=new A.aK("Build: Frictionless onboarding for merchants + staff","We build growth as operations: a clean merchant onboarding path, a staff enrollment flow that doesn\u2019t feel like surveillance, and a customer experience that never blocks checkout.\n\nThe system must integrate with existing POS rails or fall back to standalone QR infrastructure.\n\nOutcome: density compounds \u2014 each venue becomes a node in a trust network.")
B.VL=new A.aK("Launch: Hyper-local clusters to trigger network effects","We launch in neighborhood clusters where \u201cTipZero Certified\u201d has visible meaning.\n\nWe measure a systemic story: more trust \u2192 more visits \u2192 higher sponsor demand \u2192 more worker bonuses.\n\nIf the loop closes, growth compounds without paid acquisition becoming the only lever.")
B.Vp=new A.aK("Iterate: Reduce friction until the default feels inevitable","Iteration removes anything that reintroduces guilt or confusion.\n\nWe tune messaging, timing, and the post-transaction engagement so the platform stays non-adversarial \u2014 a quiet infrastructure layer.\n\nWin condition: customers stop thinking about the tip screen entirely, and merchants see retention rise.")
B.St=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.V7,B.V0,B.Wq,B.VR,B.VL,B.Vp],t.F)
B.Wm=new A.aK("Discovery: Outside liquidity, not higher percentages","TipZero monetization redesigns who funds supplemental income.\n\nMerchants can\u2019t raise wages enough without breaking demand; customers are exhausted by hidden \u201ctip inflation.\u201d The system needs outside liquidity \u2014 sponsors and post-transaction value exchange \u2014 to bridge the gap.\n\nOutput: a multi-sided value model where the customer is not the sole payer of worker stability.")
B.Vx=new A.aK("Signal: Make the value exchange instantly legible","The monetization moment works only if it reads as fair.\n\nWe prove sponsor-funded bonuses can produce predictable micro-income without hijacking checkout.\n\nSuccess metric: sponsor conversion + payout reliability + customer sentiment (no coercion).")
B.VH=new A.aK("Prototype: Bonus triggers without \u201cinvalid traffic\u201d risk","We prototype bonus triggers (reviews, lightweight engagements, sponsor matches) while designing explicitly against ad-fraud dynamics.\n\nPrinciple: the UX event (customer intent) and the revenue attribution event (ad network rules) cannot be the same thing.\n\nPrototype success: compliance-safe incentives that still feel human.")
B.Wj=new A.aK("Build: A provable ledger for bonuses and payouts","We build a performance ledger that can answer one question without ambiguity: why did this worker receive this bonus?\n\nPayout boundaries are hardened: transparent states, reconciliations, and safe-fail behaviors.\n\nThis is the infrastructure layer that prevents the system from degrading into suspicion.")
B.Vo=new A.aK("Launch: Instrument revenue quality, not vanity clicks","We launch measurement focused on integrity: payout correctness, anomaly rates, and sponsor ROI tied to real-world attention.\n\nWorker metrics track stability (volatility reduction), not spikes.\n\nIf the numbers lie, the marketplace collapses \u2014 so measurement is part of the product.")
B.V8=new A.aK("Iterate: Tune the pool toward predictable income","Iteration stabilizes worker earnings without reintroducing customer pressure.\n\nWe tune sponsor matching, bonus timing, and eligibility rules so income is steady and understandable.\n\nGoal: a dignified, multi-source supplemental income stream that feels like infrastructure.")
B.Sv=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.Wm,B.Vx,B.VH,B.Wj,B.Vo,B.V8],t.F)
B.VC=new A.aK("Discovery: Governance is the right to operate","TipZero sits inside contested terrain: tip-credit laws, tax reporting, wage optics, and platform policy.\n\nWe identify where merchants get punished (audits, disputes, confusion) and where workers lose trust (unclear payout status).\n\nOutput: a governance model that treats compliance as product design, not paperwork.")
B.VI=new A.aK("Signal: Transparent reporting without extra labor","We prove that structured supplemental income tracking reduces merchant risk.\n\nThe system produces human-readable records: what was earned, why, and how it is reported.\n\nSuccess metric: fewer disputes, faster reconciliation, higher worker trust.")
B.Vj=new A.aK("Prototype: Guardrails that don\u2019t collapse UX","We prototype overrides, corrections, sponsor rule changes, and edge-case disputes.\n\nPrinciple: dignity first \u2014 the customer never feels policed and the worker never feels tricked.\n\nIf controls are heavy-handed, adoption fails.")
B.V1=new A.aK("Build: Auditability that survives scrutiny","We build immutable histories where it matters: payout events, eligibility decisions, and sponsor matches.\n\nPolicies are explicit and versioned so changes can be explained.\n\nThis is how the product scales across jurisdictions and partners.")
B.W4=new A.aK("Launch: Operational playbooks for real-world edge cases","We ship playbooks for disputes, audit requests, payout reversals, and merchant offboarding.\n\nGovernance isn\u2019t theoretical \u2014 it\u2019s the decisions you\u2019ll be forced to make under pressure.\n\nIf playbooks are missing, the product becomes a liability.")
B.VB=new A.aK("Iterate: Policy tuning driven by friction + disputes","Iteration updates rules based on dispute patterns, abuse attempts, and regulatory shifts.\n\nChanges are communicated in plain language to workers and merchants.\n\nWin: compliance that feels like stability, not bureaucracy.")
B.Su=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.VC,B.VI,B.Vj,B.V1,B.W4,B.VB],t.F)
B.Vl=new A.aK("Discovery: Threat model the bonus economy","TipZero creates an incentive surface: wherever money flows, abuse follows.\n\nWe map threats: spoofed engagement, collusion, location fraud, and invalid traffic that can get partners banned.\n\nOutput: a risk taxonomy aligned to ad network compliance and payout integrity.")
B.Wa=new A.aK("Signal: Make abuse expensive and failure safe","We prove the system can resist obvious abuse without harming legitimate users.\n\nSecurity must not slow checkout; it must operate as invisible boundaries.\n\nSuccess metric: reduced anomaly rates with minimal false positives.")
B.Vg=new A.aK("Prototype: Secure state transitions for payouts","We prototype the lifecycle of a bonus: intent \u2192 eligibility \u2192 attribution \u2192 payout \u2192 reporting.\n\nEvery step is an explicit state transition, so exploits can\u2019t hide in undefined behavior.\n\nPrototype success: it fails safely, clearly, and recoverably.")
B.VD=new A.aK("Build: Least-privilege access + hardened boundaries","We build strict server-side validation, least-privilege access control, and defensive logging.\n\nPayout actions require strong guarantees; sponsor events require integrity checks.\n\nSecurity is the boundary that keeps the marketplace credible.")
B.VU=new A.aK("Launch: Monitoring + incident readiness","We launch monitoring for real adversaries: spikes, replay patterns, suspicious location behavior, and invalid traffic signals.\n\nIncidents are not \u201cif\u201d \u2014 they\u2019re \u201cwhen.\u201d We ship thresholds and operator tools.\n\nIf we can\u2019t respond fast, partners will leave.")
B.Wo=new A.aK(u.H,"Iteration is continuous hardening: adjust heuristics, review dependencies, and patch exploit patterns.\n\nSecurity work is not a hidden tax \u2014 it\u2019s why the system remains operable at scale.\n\nA secure bonus economy is a durable one.")
B.Sr=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.Vl,B.Wa,B.Vg,B.VD,B.VU,B.Wo],t.F)
B.Vn=new A.aK("Discovery: Engagement is dignity, not dopamine","TipZero doesn\u2019t gamify tipping. It removes coercion and replaces it with optional, value-driven participation.\n\nWe study what each actor needs: customers want privacy and control; workers want clarity and predictability; merchants want stability.\n\nOutput: an engagement model built on micro-wins that reduce awkwardness.")
B.VQ=new A.aK("Signal: Asynchronous reward moments that feel voluntary","We prove engagement without pressure: post-transaction prompts that can be ignored, sponsor matches that feel positive, and transparent worker dashboards.\n\nThe system earns attention by respecting it.\n\nSuccess metric: repeat engagement without increased checkout time.")
B.VW=new A.aK("Prototype: Post-transaction touchpoints that build trust","We prototype touchpoints after payment: leave a review, sponsor a bonus, send a thank-you.\n\nBecause the payment is complete, the user feels agency \u2014 not guilt.\n\nPrototype success: tone stays non-adversarial, respectful, fast.")
B.VX=new A.aK("Build: Performance budgets (reliability is engagement)","We build latency-first UI: fast loading, clear states, and zero ambiguity around payout outcomes.\n\nWorkers get transparent dashboards; customers get frictionless checkout; merchants get operational clarity.\n\nReliability becomes the engagement engine.")
B.W8=new A.aK("Launch: Measure loop health, not vanity metrics","We launch \u201cloop health\u201d instrumentation: return rates, sponsor funding rate, and worker income predictability.\n\nWe avoid metrics that incentivize coercive prompts.\n\nIf the loop stays healthy, the social contract is restored.")
B.W5=new A.aK("Iterate: Sharpen timing until it feels natural","Iteration tunes timing and language.\n\nWe remove anything that feels like tip-shaming and keep what feels like optional support.\n\nFinish line: rewarding service is easy \u2014 and refusing is not socially punished.")
B.Ss=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.Vn,B.VQ,B.VW,B.VX,B.W8,B.W5],t.F)
B.SV=new A.aN(B.er,[B.St,B.Sv,B.Su,B.Sr,B.Ss],t.mO)
B.Vr=new A.aK("Discovery: Close the loop, not the funnel","BridgeBound is a structural bridge across a fragmented learning ecosystem: classroom signals, parent action, student agency.\n\nWe start by mapping the real adoption constraint: parents feel blind, teachers feel overburdened, and the district feels churn risk. The win condition isn\u2019t \u201cmore usage\u201d \u2014 it\u2019s fewer high-friction moments (missed context, delayed updates, unclear next steps).\n\nOutput of this phase: a friction map that proves where \u201ccommunication overhead\u201d breaks the loop, and where a single, bite-sized insight can restore alignment within 30 seconds.")
B.We=new A.aK("Signal: Zero-latency onboarding as the wedge","For growth, BridgeBound\u2019s wedge is not a feature tour \u2014 it\u2019s an immediate translation engine.\n\nWe design the first session so a parent can see one actionable classroom micro-signal without needing an education degree. The product must feel like it replaces three tools, not adds a fourth.\n\nSuccess metric: time-to-first-clarity (TTFC) \u2014 the moment a parent says \u201cI understand what changed today and what I can do tonight.\u201d")
B.W_=new A.aK("Prototype: A relationship-driven feedback loop","We prototype the loop with three actors and one rule: micro-inputs yield macro-outputs.\n\nTeacher: one-tap observation. System: translate into parent-friendly language + suggested reinforcement. Parent: acknowledge + pick a small action. Student: sees growth framed as identity, not ranking.\n\nThe prototype is judged on emotional mechanics: does it reduce anxiety for parents, protect teacher time, and preserve student psychological safety?")
B.Wb=new A.aK("Build: Compounding growth over years, not weeks","We build for longitudinal value: data must follow the student, not the building.\n\nThat means a growth profile that can survive school transitions, hybrid models, and fragmented learning pathways \u2014 while keeping inputs light enough that teachers actually contribute.\n\nThis is where switching costs are earned ethically: the historical log of holistic growth becomes the community\u2019s shared memory.")
B.V6=new A.aK("Launch: Cohorts that prove network effects","We launch with cohorts where network effects can be observed: when parents engage asynchronously, teacher load decreases and data quality increases.\n\nThe story we measure is systemic: activation isn\u2019t a login \u2014 it\u2019s a closed loop event (teacher signal \u2192 parent action \u2192 student reinforcement \u2192 teacher confidence).\n\nIf the loop closes reliably, growth compounds without resorting to gamified tropes.")
B.W2=new A.aK("Iterate: Personalization with equity guardrails","Iteration is where BridgeBound avoids becoming another data cemetery.\n\nWe tune personalization so it improves clarity without deepening inequality: low-text, high-visual cues; multilingual affordances; and guidance that doesn\u2019t assume time, privilege, or institutional literacy.\n\nThe goal: consistent, universally accessible insight delivery that narrows the \u201cZIP Code Destiny\u201d gap rather than encoding it.")
B.Sm=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.Vr,B.We,B.W_,B.Wb,B.V6,B.W2],t.F)
B.Vm=new A.aK("Discovery: Funding mechanics, not pricing slogans","BridgeBound monetization is governed by institutional reality: per-pupil funding pressure, retention economics, and the rise of hybrid learning.\n\nWe test packaging against two buyers: districts (systemic retention + accountability) and families/homeschool ecosystems (operational backbone + portfolio proof).\n\nThe objective isn\u2019t extracting revenue \u2014 it\u2019s aligning the value metric to outcomes districts already must defend: engagement, retention, and documented growth.")
B.V5=new A.aK("Signal: Prove \u201cthe tool that replaces three others\u201d","We select one monetizable promise that is concrete: reduce conference overhead by making alignment continuous.\n\nThe signal is a before/after: fewer escalations, fewer \u201csurprise\u201d meetings, and measurable reductions in teacher time spent translating progress into parent-ready language.\n\nIf we can quantify hours saved and satisfaction gained, pricing becomes legible.")
B.VP=new A.aK("Prototype: Value metric simulation (district vs family)","We prototype entitlement boundaries with real usage rhythms: district administrators need governance and proof; parents need clarity and peace.\n\nWe simulate paywall placement around outcomes, not features: longitudinal growth reports, intervention logs, and compliance-ready exports.\n\nPrototype constraint: monetization must never increase teacher cognitive load.")
B.Vs=new A.aK("Build: Entitlements that respect trust boundaries","We build billing and entitlements as a boundary layer: pricing decisions must not contaminate student data integrity or privacy posture.\n\nOperationally: clear role-based access, auditability for institutional buyers, and a pathway for data portability (because the market demands it).\n\nThe system stays honest: what you pay for is what you can verify.")
B.V3=new A.aK("Launch: Outcome-based funding alignment","We launch offers that speak directly to market mechanics: outcome-based funding is rising, and districts need continuous documentation of growth.\n\nBridgeBound becomes the instrumented layer that makes growth legible over time \u2014 not a test-prep product, but a coordination system.\n\nLaunch success is measured in renewals driven by retained enrollment and improved parent satisfaction.")
B.Wf=new A.aK("Iterate: Packaging that scales across fragmented ecosystems","We iterate packaging for decoupled education: public, hybrid, micro-school, homeschool.\n\nThe winning monetization model is resilient across fragments because the product connects fragments.\n\nIteration focuses on lowering procurement friction while increasing perceived inevitability: \u201cThis is our student-growth home.\u201d")
B.So=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.Vm,B.V5,B.VP,B.Vs,B.V3,B.Wf],t.F)
B.VN=new A.aK("Discovery: Governance as proactive trust","Governance in BridgeBound isn\u2019t bureaucracy \u2014 it\u2019s the permission to scale a sensitive feedback loop.\n\nWe map roles (teacher, parent, admin, homeschool instructor) and the policies they\u2019re already accountable to. The constraint is clarity under scrutiny: when questioned, the system must show who saw what, when, and why.\n\nThis phase outputs a decision inventory: approvals, overrides, dispute paths, and the minimum audit trail required to keep districts confident.")
B.VS=new A.aK("Signal: Make the audit trail feel invisible","The governance wedge is paradoxical: users must feel less friction, while the institution gains more verifiable structure.\n\nWe prove this by designing workflows where teachers don\u2019t \u201cdo governance.\u201d They simply record a micro-observation, and the system handles logging, versioning, and permissioning automatically.\n\nSignal metric: reduced admin intervention per classroom, without sacrificing accountability.")
B.V4=new A.aK("Prototype: Approval flows that don\u2019t collapse UX","We prototype content approval and correction paths: what happens when a parent disputes an interpretation, or an admin needs to lock a record?\n\nWe design override paths that are explicit, rare, and legible \u2014 so governance events don\u2019t feel like random product behavior.\n\nIf governance is done right, the UX reads as calm confidence.")
B.VZ=new A.aK("Build: Immutable change history (with humane interfaces)","We build an audit event system that is immutable and queryable, but we present it in human language.\n\nThis supports two realities: parents need understandable explanations; districts need defensible records.\n\nThe outcome is governance that increases trust without demanding new behavior from already-burdened educators.")
B.Wh=new A.aK("Launch: Operational playbooks for real schools","We launch governance with playbooks: escalation paths, incident handling, and data requests.\n\nThis is where BridgeBound becomes \u201cinfrastructure,\u201d not an app.\n\nLaunch success is not just adoption \u2014 it\u2019s institutional confidence that the system holds up under audits and complaints.")
B.VO=new A.aK("Iterate: Policy tuning cadence","We iterate governance by measuring where policy creates friction or ambiguity.\n\nWe tune defaults to reduce teacher overhead, expand parent clarity, and keep administrators in control without micromanaging.\n\nThe loop: fewer disputes, faster resolution, higher trust \u2014 at scale.")
B.Sw=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.VN,B.VS,B.V4,B.VZ,B.Wh,B.VO],t.F)
B.VK=new A.aK("Discovery: Privacy is the foundation, not a checkbox","BridgeBound sits at the intersection of child development data, family context, and institutional accountability. Security is the boundary that keeps the narrative honest.\n\nWe begin with threat modeling plus FERPA/COPPA-aware privacy requirements, focusing on the true risk: not just breaches, but misuse, over-collection, and surveillance dynamics that erode student safety.\n\nThis phase defines what must never happen \u2014 and designs the system so it can\u2019t.")
B.VF=new A.aK("Signal: Trust in two minutes","We prove security to non-security users through UX: clear permission prompts, transparent data explanations, and \u201cwhy you\u2019re seeing this\u201d microcopy.\n\nAdministrators need confidence that the platform creates proactive data trust; parents need to feel safe; students need to feel respected.\n\nSignal metric: fewer privacy-related objections during onboarding and procurement.")
B.Vk=new A.aK("Prototype: Dual-stream isolation (home vs school)","We prototype the core security architecture: separate streams for school-generated signals and home-generated context.\n\nThis prevents accidental commingling and keeps the system policy-compliant without forcing manual discipline on users.\n\nWe validate that the same insight can be delivered without exposing raw sensitive inputs.")
B.Vf=new A.aK("Build: Least privilege + safe AI boundaries","We build least-privilege access control and ensure any AI/LLM components operate within strict prompting and data-minimization boundaries.\n\nSecurity includes operational safety: rate limits, audit logs, secure defaults, and principled data retention.\n\nThis is how the app supports both web and mobile responsibly: consistent security posture across platforms.")
B.Wp=new A.aK("Launch: Monitoring + incident readiness","We launch with monitoring thresholds and incident runbooks because school systems can\u2019t afford ambiguity.\n\nSecurity is treated as an operational capability: detect anomalies, respond fast, communicate clearly, and learn.\n\nLaunch success: administrators can say \u201cwe can defend this system,\u201d not just \u201cit seems secure.\u201d")
B.Vq=new A.aK(u.H,"We iterate security with a cadence: hardening sprints, dependency audits, and adversarial reviews.\n\nBecause BridgeBound is systemic infrastructure, security work is never \u201cdone.\u201d\n\nThe product remains a bridge, not a breach point \u2014 even as features expand.")
B.Sq=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.VK,B.VF,B.Vk,B.Vf,B.Wp,B.Vq],t.F)
B.V2=new A.aK("Discovery: Engagement as micro-wins, not noise","Engagement in BridgeBound is not dopamine design. It\u2019s the felt sense that progress is visible and actionable.\n\nWe map micro-win moments: a parent understands a milestone, a child sees effort reframed as growth, a teacher records a breakthrough without extra work.\n\nWe explicitly avoid surveillance vibes and ranking mechanics that undermine agency.")
B.VE=new A.aK("Signal: Clarity beats novelty","We prove that engagement can be driven by clarity: the interface must translate curriculum targets into everyday benchmarks parents can celebrate at dinner.\n\nThe product wins when it reduces anxiety and increases confidence \u2014 not when it keeps users \u201cscrolling.\u201d\n\nSignal metric: repeated weekly engagement anchored to new, bite-sized insights.")
B.Vw=new A.aK("Prototype: Motion language for understanding","We prototype interaction and motion as comprehension tools: subtle transitions that explain hierarchy, not distract.\n\nThe UX must be consumer-grade elegant (Slack/Spotify expectations) while handling institutional complexity underneath.\n\nPrototype success: users feel \u201cthis is simple,\u201d even though the system is doing hard translation work.")
B.VJ=new A.aK("Build: Performance budgets for real classrooms","We build with performance budgets: no jank, fast first paint, resilient offline behavior where appropriate.\n\nBecause BridgeBound sits on the critical path of trust, reliability is engagement.\n\nIf the product is slow, engagement collapses \u2014 not because users are impatient, but because the loop is fragile.")
B.VT=new A.aK("Launch: Instrument the loop, not vanity metrics","We launch instrumentation that measures loop health: time-to-clarity, completion of reinforcement actions, teacher input frequency, and dispute rates.\n\nWe watch where the loop breaks and treat it as a systems problem, not a marketing problem.\n\nEngagement is validated when the system reduces teacher load and increases parent confidence simultaneously.")
B.Vi=new A.aK("Iterate: Adaptive cadence without inequity","We iterate content cadence and difficulty adaptively, but with equity guardrails: the system must work for parents with limited time, English fluency, or institutional familiarity.\n\nThe goal is durable engagement rooted in empowerment \u2014 not behavioral addiction.\n\nWhen done right, engagement becomes the visible footprint of a repaired ecosystem.")
B.Sn=new A.aN(B.bk,[B.V2,B.VE,B.Vw,B.VJ,B.VT,B.Vi],t.F)
B.SY=new A.aN(B.er,[B.Sm,B.So,B.Sw,B.Sq,B.Sn],t.mO)
